ur household will eat in any 24 hour period.","Among the 170,000+ recipes available with Big Oven, some are included with the software, but many can be accessed on their site by registering for a free account. BigOven’s huge recipe archive can be accessed though their application by clicking the Web button on the left side of the screen. Search by main ingredient, cuisine, special considerations, preparation method, season/occasion and course/dish. All recipes include ratings, user reviews and nutrient information.","BigOven has a powerful integrated meal planning tool with drag and drop functionality for adding recipes to the meal calendar. If you put the recipe into the wrong meal plan, no worries, simply drag and drop to move the recipe to the appropriate meal window. When adding recipes to your meal calendar this menu planner is a step ahead, and prompts you to how many servings you’d like when adding the recipe to your calendar. Choose from Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, and Snacks/Other, and easily stay on top of whichever date you’re working on by clicking on the integrated calendar graphic.","BigOven does a great job of providing detailed nutritional information on all the ingredients listed in their recipe database. By clicking on the Nutrients tab in the left column of the meal planning software, a powerful nutrient-finder tool is displayed. Search the ingredient database and find the nutritional information on thousands of items, including calories from fat, total fat, cholesterol, carbohydrates, protein, fiber and potassium.","Meal plans, shopping lists, and even a “Month at a Glance” meal calendar can be printed for easy reference. You also have the option to publish recipes and menus to your personal website (free when you register at BigOven.com), email them to family, friends or customers, or send them directly to your PDA.","By navigating to the Tools &gt; Create Shopping List from Menu Plan, BigOven will instantly generate a shopping list according to the ingredients on your menu plan. Select which recipes you’d like to focus on and include only them in your shopping list. You can also manually select which individual recipes and ingredients you’d like to shop for, including telling you which you already have (an excellent tool for avoiding redundancies in your cupboard). This software can organize shopping lists by aisle, but the tool we really liked is the ability to create lists by date range. So, if you create a month of meal plans you can choose to have a grocery list created for only one week of meal plans. After your list is complete, either print or upload it to your iPhone, iPad, Windows or Android phone.","In addition to printing out recipe index cards with BigOven, you can print several other useful items as well while using this meal planning software. BigOven is on the cutting edge of mobile technology. Their highly popular iPhone, iPad and Android apps have millions of downloads and bring meal planning software to your phone by enabling meal planning on-the-go. These apps are especially useful for providing automatic shopping lists that don’t require printing. Instead, have your detailed shopping list imported directly to your phone. You will never have to write another shopping list again.","BigOven is an incredibly easy meal planning software to use in a large part because of it’s drag and drop capabilities, secondly because of its easy navigation. At the top of the screen there are large buttons to help you easily access the most commonly-used functions in the program. On the left side of the screen is a column listing the recipe database.","BigOven has two impressive wizard tools you’re sure to enjoy. The first tool is their Idea Wizard, a handy widget that begins by asking what type of meal you’d like to make: Main Entrée, Salad, Appetizer, Dessert, Side Dish or Breakfast. After choosing the type of meal, BigOven asks you the main ingredient (pork chops, hamburger, etc.), any special instructions, and once received, BigOven displays hundreds of recipes you can make with your main ingredient. Meal planning software has never been more ingenious.","Another wizard tool we found useful in the BigOven is their Leftover Wizard, a surprisingly smart widget that helps you figure out new and unheard of recipes for whichever three ingredients you put into it. Go ahead, add any three ingredients. You’ll be impressed by the variety of recipes you can use for your leftovers by using the BigOven recipe database.","BigOven makes finding assistance a stress-free process whether you have a question about their meal planning software or if you need to contact the customer service department directly. If you’d like to find the answer to your question using their help guide, there are several options. First, you can check-out their user guide which comes standard with every copy of BigOven. Second, a helpful list of FAQs can be found on their site answering over 75 commonly asked questions.To contact their customer service department you can contact them via email, or via a support ticket system, that can also be found on their site.","BigOven does an impressive job of making sure they stay connected to their users. They have an active Facebook page with seasonal recipes posted each day. BigOven also has a Twitter account and if user forums are more up your alley, you’re sure to love their Cooking How-To forums found in the Community section of their site. Discover a variety of unique cooking ideas and techniques in this active community of BigOven users."]},"id":"9a9e5619-7c3d-4081-9aa6-5582c1ade70b","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"15ba31fe-b034-44a1-b5b4-f3e908e42e0d","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Big Oven is a jam-packed recipe and meal planning software with ingenious extras that can’t be found anywhere else. From their Leftover and Ideas Wizards, their huge 170,000+ recipe database, online integration, to the drag and drop meal planning capabi